ğŸ”¤ 1ï¸âƒ£ TEXT FORMULAS
ğŸ”¹ LOWER()

Purpose: Converts text to lowercase

Syntax:

=LOWER(text)


Example:

=LOWER("AUS")


Result:

aus

ğŸ”¹ UPPER()

Purpose: Converts text to uppercase

Syntax:

=UPPER(text)


Example:

=UPPER("aus")


Result:

AUS

ğŸ”¹ PROPER()

Purpose: Capitalizes first letter of each word

Syntax:

=PROPER(text)


Example:

=PROPER("aus")


Result:

Aus

ğŸ”¹ LEFT()

Purpose: Extract characters from the left

Syntax:

=LEFT(text, number_of_characters)


Example:

=LEFT("Boxes", 2)


Result:

Bo

ğŸ”¹ RIGHT()

Purpose: Extract characters from the right

Syntax:

=RIGHT(text, number_of_characters)


Example:

=RIGHT("Boxes", 2)


Result:

es

ğŸ”¹ MID()

Purpose: Extract characters from the middle

Syntax:

=MID(text, start_position, number_of_characters)


Example:

=MID("Boxes", 2, 2)


Result:

ox

ğŸ”¹ LEN()

Purpose: Counts number of characters

Syntax:

=LEN(text)


Example:

=LEN("Boxes")


Result:

5

ğŸ”¹ TRIM()

Purpose: Removes extra spaces

Syntax:

=TRIM(text)


Example:

=TRIM("  aus  ")


Result:

aus

ğŸ”¹ FIND()

Purpose: Finds position of text (case-sensitive)

Syntax:

=FIND(find_text, within_text)


Example:

=FIND("o","Boxes")


Result:

2

ğŸ”¹ SUBSTITUTE()   

Purpose: Replaces text

Syntax:

=SUBSTITUTE(text, old_text, new_text)


Example:

=SUBSTITUTE("aus","aus","AUS")


Result:

AUS


